      <h1 class='title'>House of Lords Reform</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 22 April 2004 vol 420 c26WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_26ws' title='Col. 26WS &mdash; HC Deb 22 April 2004 vol 420 c26WS' name='column_26ws' href='#column_26ws' rel='bookmark'>26WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution'>
        <a name='S6CV0420P2_20040422_CWS_6'>  </a>
        <blockquote class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <cite class='member author entry-title unmatched-member'>The Secretary of State, Department for Constitutional Affairs and Lord Chancellor (Lord Falconer of Thoroton)</cite>
          <p class="first-para">I have today published the responses to the consultation paper<span class="italic">"Next steps for the House of Lords",</span> and a Government summary of these. Copies of the summary have been placed in the Libraries of both Houses. The individual responses are available on the Department for Constitutional Affairs' website, <span class="underline">www.dca.gov.uk.</span></p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
